result.name: 上海一品香菜館

reviews.text: Traditional and good shanghaiese restaurant

Must say it's been quite disappointing. It looks like a well established restaurant,  expectations were high. Too bad the fried rice was quite a let down, the ham and the chicken they used wasn't fresh enough,   the amount of egg used was not enough to give the fried rice the taste snd smell it needed. The skin of the dumpling wasn't strong enough to be picked up using chopsticks without rupturing. Sounded like a total disaster, but the set lunch is good, the taste of the dishes were decent, neither too strong or too weak. Oh and the tea they served is good. I will give the place another try, and let you know.
Good family restaurant
ok not bad
Not the most delicious or delicate shanghainese food. But it's a Shanghai family run business which has been here for over 20 years and the staff are always very welcoming. Will come back again.

reviews.text: 星期六午市還有客飯及吾使加一，算便宜
有貓在食店內，隻貓瞓在“整飽枱”的麵粉旁邊😡😡衛生有問題😡😡
環境和食物一般，價錢便宜，小籠包和鍋貼較好，適合懷舊，有家庭感覺
老香港上海菜 ~ 小籠包好好食 ,豬扒粗炒好好味, 仲有醉雞添, 醃篤鮮都做得好好!
家庭式小店，味道傳統，質素仍可改善。
